      • ANCHOR

        public static final ExecutionVariable ANCHOR
        When used, this means the command's execution may vary, depending on the anchor (feet or eyes) of the execution.
        When modified, this means the command execution anchor is changed. Only applies to commands which utilize local coordinates.

      • COUNT

        public static final ExecutionVariable COUNT
        When used, this means the command will do different things, depending on how many times it is run. Realistically, this variable is assumed to always be used. As such, there is no need to mark this as used in a usage ExecutionVariableMap, only in modification maps, such as those of execute sub-commands.
        When modified, this means the number of executions of the command is changed.

      • CONDITION

        public static final ExecutionVariable CONDITION
        When used, this means the command's execution will depend on a condition. Realistically, this variable is assumed to always be used. As such, there is no need to mark this as used in a usage ExecutionVariableMap, only in modification maps, such as those of execute sub-commands.
        When modified, this means the command may or may not run. This is practically the same as setting the count to zero or one, and is modified when conditions are applied, or a selector which could return no entities is used.
